Consistent with other studies, to examine object-based attention effects, we collapsed across (the non-significant main effects of) rectangle orientations and cue-target ISIs. Using a one-way ANOVA, we found a significant effect of cue condition (F(2, 526) = 80.6, p < .01). Response times were fastest when the target appeared at the cued location \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
